    "description": "Verification run of economic friction parameters on the FULL 60-node network.\ntargeted_sweep3 on the lite network showed v27 winning all 16 scenarios at econ=0.65, commit=0.35. However, targeted_sweep1 on the full network showed v26 winning at similar parameters. This 4-scenario verification tests the corner cases on the full network to determine:\n\n  1. Does the full network produce different outcomes? (likely v26 wins)\n  2. Do friction parameters matter on the full network? (probably not)\n\nIf all 4 corners show v26_dominant, it confirms:\n  - Network size matters for outcome thresholds\n  - Friction still doesn't affect outcomes\n\nIf outcomes vary, a full 16-scenario re-run may be needed.\n",
